				=a little off the topics here= <br>  <br> I'll agree that being rude doesn't make one evil.  A paladin can be rude and harsh to those that does not fall into &quot;his&quot; principles.  I think it's perfectly alright and roleplaying if a paladin says to a dark elf female necro &quot;begone! you wreched whore of soandso god!  I would not have the likes of you in my presence!&quot;.  But then some people would argue that is against the PNP rule.  *sigh* ...oh, well....we need to work on what we are given.... <br>  <br> As for evil race roleplaying evil, I don't think it is absolutely necessary for PvP to be involved.  In a PvP environment, the maturity of the players is the one single most important factor to ensure proper RP is done before PvP is engaged.  You can't expect that sort of maturity in EQ.  However, one can roleplaying evil by how the character words his conversation, and by his constant actions (emotes).  It is limited, yes, but one can always be creative.   <br>  <br> A few ideas for emotes I can think of: <br>  <br> evil gnomes/halflings: <br> /em rubs his hands in a greedy anticipation. <br>  <br> evil insane necro gnomes: <br> /em throws back his head and cackles at %t. <br> /em stares at %t with a hint of insanity in his eyes. <br>  <br> I believe if you repeat these custom emotes enough times around your group mates, they sure will get a creepy feeling about grouping with an evil char.  
